artifacts.action_items:
[
  {
    "task": "Provide £149 million in funding for 2019-20",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "2019-20",
    "evidence": "The meeting discusses the financial sustainability of the higher education sector in Wales, focusing on the challenges faced by universities, the impact of demographic changes, and the role of the Higher Education Funding Council for Wales (HEFCW) in supporting the sector."
  },
  {
    "task": "Work with the sector to improve the accessibility of information on income and expenditure",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: The reporting of the income and expenditure is largely provided, probably more so in narrative form in the accounts and the financial statements and annual reports of institutions."
  },
  {
    "task": "Provide £15 million in innovation funding to support universities in accessing UKRI funding",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "2020-21",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: One aspect that we do intend to fund—and this is from Diamond, as well as Reid—is to place funding back into the system for innovation. We're consulting currently, with the intention, if the funding is available to us, clearly, in the year 2020-21, to provide £15 million back into the sector in innovation funding."
  },
  {
    "task": "Monitor each university's estates strategy and financing",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Angela Burns AM: Considering how much is invested in their estates, are you happy that each university's estates strategy and its financing is prudent and has appropriate governing-body oversight in place?"
  },
  {
    "task": "Maintain QR funding at the same level as previous years",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "2019-20",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: We have maintained QR, which is our funding for research, quality research, and postgraduate research, at least at the same levels of £76 million, as it's been that in previous years."
  },
  {
    "task": "Increase part-time funding by £1 million to £26 million",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "2019-20",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: We've allocated £26.5 million in 2019-20 to support part-time provision, and we have been able in 2019-20 to fund some growth."
  },
  {
    "task": "Develop a vision for research and innovation",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Dr David Blaney: And, then, there's also the recommendation from Reid that Wales needs to be better embedded in the conversations that are going on on a UK-wide basis, so the Welsh Government has established a presence in London in respect of research, and we have a colleague in HEFCW who is fractionally embedded in the United Kingdom Research and Innovation specifically to respond to that recommendation."
  },
  {
    "task": "Provide £28 million of investment in student support-related activities",
    "owner": "Universities",
    "deadline": "2019-20",
    "evidence": "Dr David Blaney: The sector has committed over £28 million of investment in student support-related activities from the fee and access plans, and that includes, in many instances, bursaries that are designed to help students cope with the costs of accommodation and the cost of living more generally."
  }
]

